  "created": "2025-10-08",
  "description": "DNA replication initiation in E. coli occurs at the origin of replication (oriC) through a highly regulated process involving DnaA protein, which recognizes and binds to DnaA boxes, leading to DNA melting at the AT-rich DUE region and assembly of the replisome. This process is tightly controlled to ensure replication occurs only once per cell cycle.",
  "id": "ecoli_dna_replication_initiation",
  "keywords": [
    "DNA replication",
    "oriC",
    "DnaA protein",
    "replication initiation",
    "DnaB helicase",
    "cell cycle control",
    "SeqA",
    "hemimethylation"
  ],
  "lastUpdated": "2025-10-08",
  "logicGates": {
    "and": 0,
    "not": 1,
    "or": 0
  },
  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    Start([Cell Cycle Signal]) --> DnaACheck{DnaA-ATP<br/>Available?}\n    DnaACheck -->|No| Wait[Wait for ATP<br/>Regeneration]\n    DnaACheck -->|Yes| Binding[DnaA-ATP Binds to<br/>DnaA Boxes at oriC]\n    \n    Binding --> Recognition[Recognition of<br/>9-bp DnaA Boxes]\n    Recognition --> Oligomer[DnaA Oligomer<br/>Formation]\n    Oligomer --> Unwinding[DNA Unwinding at<br/>AT-rich DUE Region]\n    \n    Unwinding --> DnaB[DnaB Helicase<br/>Loading]\n    DnaB --> DnaC[DnaC Chaperone<br/>Assists Loading]\n    DnaC --> Hexamer[DnaB Hexamer<br/>Formation]\n    \n    Hexamer --> Primase[DnaG Primase<br/>Recruitment]\n    Primase --> Primer[RNA Primer<br/>Synthesis]\n    Primer --> PolIII[DNA Pol III<br/>Holoenzyme Recruitment]\n    \n    PolIII --> Replisome[Active Replisome<br/>Assembly]\n    Replisome --> Elongation[DNA Replication<br/>Elongation Begins]\n    \n    Elongation --> Regulation[Negative Regulation]\n    Regulation --> SeqA[SeqA Protein Binds<br/>Hemimethylated oriC]\n    Regulation --> DnaAADP[DnaA-ATP to<br/>DnaA-ADP Conversion]\n    SeqA --> PreventReinitiation[/Prevent Reinitiation/]\n    DnaAADP --> PreventReinitiation\n    \n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n    style B fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style C fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style III fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style A fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style AADP fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style PreventReinitiation fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff",
  "name": "DNA Replication Initiation at oriC",
  "notGates": 1,
  "notes": "This model focuses on the core initiation process. Contains 1 OR logic gate (DnaA-ATP availability check). The ATP/ADP switch of DnaA is critical for ensuring once-per-cell-cycle replication. All 24 nodes are uniquely identified and colored according to the 7-color Programming Framework.",
